<p><b>Wendell Berry</b> (born August 5, 1934, <a href="/wiki/Henry_County,_Kentucky" title="Henry County, Kentucky">Henry County, Kentucky</a>) is an American <a href="/wiki/Man_of_letters" title="Man of letters" class="mw-redirect">man of letters</a>, academic, cultural and <a href="/wiki/Economic" title="Economic" class="mw-redirect">economic</a> critic, and <a href="/wiki/Farmer" title="Farmer">farmer</a>. He is a prolific author of <a href="/wiki/Novel" title="Novel">novels</a>, <a href="/wiki/Short_story" title="Short story">short stories</a>, poems, and <a href="/wiki/Essay" title="Essay">essays</a>. He is also an elected member of the <a href="/wiki/Fellowship_of_Southern_Writers" title="Fellowship of Southern Writers">Fellowship of Southern Writers</a>.</p>
